<DOC><DOCNO> AP890910-0011 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-10-89 0328EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u a BC-HelicopterSearch     09-10 0154</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Helicopter Search,0158</SECOND><HEAD>Idaho Guard Members Reported Missing When Helicopter Fails To Return</HEAD><DATELINE>BOISE, Idaho (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Four Idaho National Guard crew members werereported missing Saturday after their helicopter failed to returnfrom a routine training flight.   The crew left Gowen Field, adjacent to Boise Municipal Airport,at about 5 p.m. Saturday and were due to return by 6:30 p.m., said1st Lt. Michael Gollaher, Gowen Field deputy public affairs officer.   Four aircraft searched for the missing crew and helicopterSaturday night before the search was called off at midnight.Gollaher said the search would resume early today.   The pilot and crew were considered experienced, and are assignedto the 183rd Aviation Attack Helicopter Battalion. The missinghelicopter is a UH-1H ``Huey,'' a Vietnam-era aircraft about 20years old.   Gollaher said there is no history of unusual mechanical problemswith the missing aircraft. The names of the crew members were notreleased.</TEXT></DOC>